st%20of%20all%2C%20I%20think%20that%20they're%20just%20flat-out%20delicious%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Bussiness%20Insider.%20And%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20you%20have%20these%20ferments%20in%20your%20fridge%20at%20home%2C%20it%20becomes%20really%20easy%20to%20eat%20healthily%20on%20a%20regular%20basis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFermented%20foods%2C%20such%20as%20yogurt%2C%20sourdough%20bread%2C%20and%20kombucha%2C%20are%20created%20when%20live%20bacteria%20are%20added%20to%20food%20or%20drinks%20like%20vegetables%2C%20milk%2C%20or%20tea.%20They%20often%20contain%20%26quot%3Bgood%26quot%3B%20microbes%20and%20are%20known%20to%20increase%20the%20diversity%20of%20the%20gut%20microbiome%2C%20a%20sign%20of%20a%20healthy%20gut%20that's%20linked%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgut-health-boost-overall-digestion-better-moods-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealth%20benefits%20all%20over%20the%20body%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20diversity%20of%20the%20gut%20microbiome%20is%20directly%20linked%20to%20the%20diversity%20of%20your%20diet%2C%26quot%3B%20Zilber%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20experts%20recommend%20aiming%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feating-30-plants-a-week-gut-health-easier-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E30%20different%20plant%20foods%20a%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20promote%20gut%20health%2C%20there's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fcell%2Ffulltext%2FS0092-8674(21)00754-6%3F_returnURL%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Flinkinghub.elsevier.com%252Fretrieve%252Fpii%252FS0092867421007546%253Fshowall%253Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20suggest%20that%20fermented%20food%20increases%20microbiome%20diversity%20even%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZilber%2C%20who%20is%20based%20in%20Copenhagen%20but%20grew%20up%20in%20Toronto%2C%20made%20his%20name%20in%20the%20culinary%20world%20doing%20%26quot%3Bthe%20wildest%20forms%20of%20experimental%20fermentation%26quot%3B%20at%20Noma%2C%20which%20is%20due%20to%20close%20in%20late%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20at%20home%2C%20he%20likes%20to%20keep%20it%20classic.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20kind%20of%20a%20bit%20straight%20and%20narrow%20with%20ferments.%20I%20like%20the%20flavor%20to%20shine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Bussiness%20Insider.%20Plus%2C%20they're%20the%20most%20versatile%20to%20cook%20with%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZilber%20shared%20the%20five%20go-to%20ferments%20he%20has%20%26quot%3Bon%20constant%20rotation%26quot%3B%20to%20enhance%20his%20meals%20and%20tend%20to%20his%20microbiome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f22a90b5-ca58-494a-98a0-07c305f4bac4%5C%22%3EKimchi%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKimchi%20is%20a%20lacto-ferment%2C%20meaning%20it's%20made%20using%20lactic%20acid-producing%20bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20ingredient%20is%20napa%20cabbage%2C%20and%20it%20often%20contains%20other%20crunchy%20vegetables%2C%20and%20Korean%20chile%20flakes%20or%20gochujang%20paste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20method%20typically%20involves%20soaking%20the%20leaves%20in%20salty%20water%20for%20around%20a%20day%20before%20the%20other%20ingredients%20are%20added.%20Then%20you%20leave%20it%20on%20the%20counter%20for%20a%20week%20or%20two%2C%20Zilber%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20previously%20shared%20his%20easy%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feasy-kimchi-sauerkraut-pickle-recipes-by-ex-noma-fermentation-chef-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20at-home%20kimchi%20recipe%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2290b331b8-0864-4ce4-b48e-c1604b94b8cc%5C%22%3ESauerkraut%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20forkful%20of%20sauerkraut%20hovering%20over%20a%20white%20bowl%20of%20sauerkraut.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c366841aa2ac29ee322b00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESauerkraut%20is%20a%20staple